## 10. v0 transitional carve-outs (documented exceptions)

The pre-migration codebase has documented violations of this rule. They are **frozen** — no new code is allowed to compound them; they are scheduled for cleanup per the monorepo retro:

| Exception | Where | Removed in |
|---|---|---|
| UI in `components/` not `src/ui/` | `zedos/nextjs_space/components/**` | Phase 2 (P2.7 of monorepo retro) |
| `lib/credits.ts`, `lib/ai-service.ts`, `lib/auth-options.ts`, `lib/config.ts` parallel runtime | `zedos/nextjs_space/lib/**` | Phase 2 (P2.2 — P2.5 of monorepo retro) |
| `prisma/schema.prisma` co-located with the app | `zedos/nextjs_space/prisma/` | Phase 1 (P1.6) → Phase 2 (P2.6) |
| `next.config.js: eslint.ignoreDuringBuilds: true` | `zedos/nextjs_space/next.config.js` | Phase 0 (P0.5) |
| `tsconfig.json: strict: false`, `noImplicitAny: false` | `zedos/nextjs_space/tsconfig.json` | Phase 1 (P1.1, P1.5) |
| 117 `as any` casts across `src/`, `app/`, `lib/` | various | Phase 1 (P1.4) |

Treat each exception as a **freeze**: do not add to the count, do not introduce parallel violations elsewhere, and prefer fixes that reduce the count whenever a touched file is in scope.

---

## 11. Migration path to monorepo

When the time comes:

1. Move `src/domain/` → `packages/domain/`
2. Move `src/application/` → `packages/application/`
3. Move `src/contracts/` → `packages/contracts/`
4. Move `src/shared/` → `packages/shared/`
5. Update workspace protocol in `tsconfig.json`
6. No code changes — purely folder moves.

